<Author>Goldig
<Content>Couldn't ask for more We spent 3 nights here and were very pleased with everything.Front desk manager extremely helpful. Large room in main building as well as extremely large bathroom and everything cleaned every day. We had a rear room so no noise at all.Best part is it's location on U line 6 (easy in from Tegel airport with a short bus ride to the U-bahn 6 line at first) which crosses U-bahn 2 at the corner. Bus to Potsdamer Platz where one can change to bus to Hauptbahnhof passes the hotel. Easy access to Alexanderplatz by bus or U-bahn and a stone's throw to Check-point Charlie Museum. Oh yes, the breakfast was very good including sausages and eggs as well as cold items and fruit. The hotel is very plain but just perfect for sightseeing. The price of 99euros w/breakfast was really very reasonable.The 72 hour A/B zones travel card makes hopping on all means of transportaion within the city well worth it's purchase including getting in from the airport. Finding the office to buy the card at Tegel was the only challenge! There is so much to see in the new Berlin! 
