<Author>Lon39don39
<Content>Excellent staff, great hotel We booked through the Hauptbahnhof infostore on arrival in Berlin and couldn't have been more pleased. The hotel is the former Bulgarian embassy guest quarters and still has wonderful elements of Soviet austerity in its design. We stayed in the suite block at the back of the hotel across a courtyard. The rooms were large, beds comfortable, bathroom spotless and the rate fantastic. You feel like you're staying in a real part of Berlin history. Breakfast was good. More importantly, you couldn't find more helpful staff than those at the Kubrat - incredibly attentive, courteous and thoughtful. The location is fantastic: two minutes walk from Checkpoint Charlie and the Gendarmenmarkt, 15 minutes to the Brandenburg Gate or the Museumsinsel. U-Bahn station Stadtmitte is 1 minute away and takes you to Prenzlauerberg in one direction and Sch枚neberg and Ku-Damm in the other. Bus M48 runs directly outside to Alexanderplatz. There are good upmarket restaurants in the Gendarmenmarkt and cheaper ones south of Checkpoint Charlie. 
