<Author>Annie79
<Content>Great location  My husband and I and our 25-year-old son have just returned from a two-week stay at Hotel Kubrat. We were favourably impressed, and at 135 Euros a night it was excellent value. We had a 2-bedroom apartment in a separate building behind the main building and through a parking lot. The building was older, but perfectly clean and well kept. The apartment had IKEA-type furnishings. There were 2 bathrooms, one with just a toilet and sink, the other with a toilet, sink and bathtub with a hand-held shower, which we found a bit awkward. There was a large living room and a balcony. There was also a mini-bar fridge stocked with beer, water, wine, etc. that were reasonably priced, and the fridge was also large enough to hold items we purchased elsewhere.The included breakfast buffet was very good. The restaurant staff were always pleasant and smiling, as were the front desk staff. We found their English to be somewhat limited, but adequate (this is Germany after all!). We also appreciated the free internet in the stairway off the main lobby, and the fact that we could buy transit passes at the front desk and just charge it to our bill.The location was excellent, just steps from the Stadtmitte U-bahn station and within close walking distance of lots of restaurants and shopping. It was also within reasonable walking distance of many sites, including Museuminsel and Potsdamer Platz.The only inconvenience with this hotel was the fact that they would only give us one key for the apartment, and with 3 adults, we were not always coming and going at the same time. However, this problem was manageable with some advance planning. 
