<Author>gin76
<Content>Great appartment - perfect location Our family of three adults stayed at Kubrat for two nights in august 07. We made our reservation through the tourist information office at the Brandenburg Gate.We got appartment no 6 in a building just through the backyard parking place (鈧?6/day). The appartment was huge - two big bedrooms, a large livingroom with a nice balcony, a bathroom with toilet, and another separate wc, and a kitchen with fridge and a sink. Though the appartment could need some new carpeting and some paintwork, it was perfect for our stay.The location is great. Approx. 50 m from Checkpoint Charlie, and with Potsdamer Platz, Unter den Linden, Brandenburg Gate and Reichstag within a distance of 800 m, the Kubrat Hotel is the perfect starting point for a Berlin experience.The staff was very nice and polite, and we got warm smiles from both the reception staff and the lovely breakfast-fraulein. Not all of them are very good in English, but with a little German and a little English, it's OK. Breakfast is also OK, but could be better. All in all, though, the Kubrat Hotel is great value. 
