<Content>Good Value in the Heart of Berlin Hotel Kubrat Berlin Mitte was a pleasant surprise. The rooms are spacious, well kept, and comfortable. You are within walking distance of some nice restaurants and Check Point Charlie, plus the subway is just around the corner. The breakfast buffet was a delicious standard European fair within a nice atrium overlooking the street. The staff was courteous and helpful. Beds were a bit hard and the free internet a bit slow. But overall it is a good value in the heart of Berlin. I would stay there again. 
