<Author>KY_Traveller
<Content>Consider Hotel Kubrat My wife and I spent seven days at the Hotel Kubrat and were very satisfied. The room was large and comfortable. The shower was in one room, the toilet and sink in another. Both of these rooms were separated by a door from the rest of the room where the beds and a sitting area were located. Even though our room faced busy Leipziger Strasse, the street noise seldom bothered us. The included breakfast was varied, although it never changed from day to day. The reception desk was staffed 24 hours a day, and they were very courteous. Since their English was far better than my limited German, we never had problems communicating. In spite of the fact that the other hotel guests were German, we always felt like we fit in with the crowd. The location, near the Stadtmitte U-bahn, was very convenient and within walking distance of the Gendarmenmarkt area. The next cross street from the hotel is Friedrichstrasse whose shopping opportunities reminded us of Michigan Ave. in Chicago. 
